# System Architecture

```text
User Request
      |
      v
+-------------------+
| Global WAF Layer  |
+-------------------+
      |
      v
+-------------------+
| SQLi Detection    |
+-------------------+
      |
      v
+-------------------+
| Brute-force Layer |
+-------------------+
      |
      v
+-------------------+
| Flask Application |
+-------------------+
      |
      v
Database / Response
```

---

# Why Different ML Models?

## Logistic Regression for SQLi

Chosen because:

* SQLi payloads are largely keyword-based
* Works well with sparse TF-IDF text features
* Low inference latency
* Interpretable and lightweight

## Random Forest for XSS

Chosen because:

* XSS payloads are highly non-linear
* Better handling of obfuscated scripts
* Captures complex feature interactions
* More robust against noisy inputs

